<br>
Here's the Story...<br>
<br>
The year is 2317, the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics controls all of Earth. The United American Republic (UAR) has been forced into deep space, making it’s home planet Terras, New Earth, the second planet in the Betelgeuse system. <br>
<br>
It was not always like this, and yet it was inevitable. The world progressed as it should have, everything as you or I would know true happened, until 1972. In 1972, the USSR with it’s military might, “annexed” nearly all of Asia. Because this was outwardly a political arrangement, done with much smiling and shaking of hands, no action could be taken by NATO. Many of the Politicians who opposed these annexations met in an undisclosed location in Israel to try and stop them. A Palestinian suicide bomber walked in on the meeting and killed them all. Much money was used to stop a full investigation.<br>
<br>
In 1989, the Berlin wall fell, this time not hailing the collapse of the Soviet Union, but hailing the near total conquest of Eurasia. World War Three progressed on from there, dragging out over fifty years of intermittent combat, just barely missing becoming a nuclear holocaust. In 2053, The remnants of NATO, now calling themselves the UAR, boarded a fleet of short range colonizer starships and fled to Mars. They held out on the red planet, surviving many attacks by the USSR. For eighty-five years the UAR worked on Mars, until their task was complete. A probe was launched, equipped with a drive system capable of making the trip to the most distant known inhabitable planet from earth and the USSR, the second planet in the Betelgeuse system, in one instantaneous jump. The probe reached it’s destination, and went into action. With the exit of a jump gate system in position, the UAR was quick to deploy the entrance. As the battle fleet of the USSR descended upon Mars, the UAR fleet made the jump to Betelgeuse. After the last ship passed through the gate, the gate exit was detonated,.<br>
<br>
Now, two hundred sixty-four years after Earth fell to communism, Terras has become the capitol of 56 inhabited planets under the jurisdiction of the UAR, under President Nicholas Maris. Earth and over forty-two planets stand under the feet of “Comrade” Josef Zabarski. Hundreds of different planets and asteroids stand under the control of no-one, save the pirate lords and miners who run them. <br>
<br>
It is in this war torn universe that you make your appearance. Shall you be the instrument of the liberation of the planets under the heel of the USSR? Will you finally crush the UAR? Will you make a legend of yourself in some other way? Or will you fade into obscurity? <br>
<br>
Make your choice. <br>
<br>
The time is now. <br>
<br>
If that sounds appetizing to you, then come on over!<br>
